defaultAlthough failure to comply with the other rules of The Highway Code will not, in itself, cause a person to be prosecuted, The Highway Code may be used in evidence in any court proceedings under the Traffic Acts (see 
defaultThe road user and the law
default) to establish liability. This includes rules which use advisory wording such as ‘should/should not’ or ‘do/do not’.”
