default4B
defaultThe GB accident data for 2011 shows 979 deaths in non-built up areas compared with 816 for built up areas. Most 
defaultdeaths occurred on ‘A’ roads. For cycling ‘A’ roads pose a high risk and changes are needed urgently. The above suggestions could help lower the number killed and relate directly to the provision of cycling infrastructure.
